cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the automatic segmentation of brain tumors from MRI data. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as the approach presented involves the use of a directed 3D graph and the calculation of the minimal s-t cut. The neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as deep learning techniques are often used in medical image analysis. Finally, the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category may be relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of MRI data.
